evaluation.response:
it sounds like you're having some really tough thoughts and feeling like you're just another bill to pay, which could feel like a huge burden. Try not to internalize that, though. Your value lies in who you are as a person, not as a financial burden.&#x20;

If you feel comfortable, reach out to your school counselor, a trusted friend, or a suicide prevention hotline. They can offer some support and guidance to help you work through this.&#x20;

Also, know that all those people you mentioned still care about you. They probably just aren't sure how to react or support you. But as for you feeling like a burden, you're definitely not. You can be so precious to the people around you.

lot's of people have felt this way and believed they were worthless. It clears up eventually, boy.&#x20;
